Dear Students👦🏽👧🏻👧🏿👦🏼,

Today🌞 we announce✍🗣 a new enrollment and payment💸💵💰 policy 🤔😳that goes into effect 👉🏼this 👈🏼 fall 🏈📚🖊. This new 🆕 policy helps ensure 👍🏼that the available seats🛋🎎 in a class🏢 are maximized 👀💯💯👌effectively and fairly 😎😏👍🏼.

Cancel for Non-Payment Policy

Effective fall 2️⃣0️⃣1️⃣6️⃣ 🔜, the campus has approved the Cancel 🙅🏼❌for Non-Payment🚫💰💸 policy. Under this new 🆕 policy, students 👦🏼👧🏽👲🏿👳🏼 are required to pay🙄😭😱 20 percent 📈😥 or more 💀💀💀 of their tuition 💸💷 and fees 💸💸💸(including nonresident tuition 🇰🇷🇨🇭🇲🇽) by 📅August 19, 2016 📅in order to remain registered 🔓🔒in their enrolled classes✒️✏️📝 for fall semester 2016.📓📕📒

How it Works

Undergraduate students 👦🏼👧🏿👱🏿 who have not🙅🏼 paid💳💸 at least 20 percent📈📊 of their tuition and fees💴💵💶 by the August 19 ⏳⌛️deadline⏳⌛️ will have their enrollment in all classes 👀, including those waitlisted😟😖, canceled 😱😱😱one day before instruction begins😭🔫. After students are canceled❌🚫, waitlists will be automatically processed 🗃🗳🗄to fill in open class seats🆙🆗.

Fall 2016 📆🗓financial aid 🏧💸will be released🎈🎈 to eligible students 👯👫👭beginning ✌🏼August 15, 2016✌🏼️. You can monitor 👀👀 your aid 💸💵💴disbursements in the 🔑My Finances section of CalCentral🔑. If sufficient aid 💰💳is ready to disburse 🌦☔️and will cover at least 20 percent📈📊 of your tuition and fees by the payment deadline🚫❌, you will notbe subject to Cancel for Non-Payment😩💯🙏. If you are still at risk for Cancel for Non-Payment, CalCentral will alert you.😳🙄

Students👦👧👨👲 who are canceled ❌🙅are eligible to re-enroll in classes with available seats🛋🎎 starting August 24📬📪📫. Tuition and fees 💸💵💴will be re-assessed, and payment will be due the following day.🗓🔜

What You Need to Do

If you👈🏼😜 are receiving financial aid 💸💵💴or other awards🎁🏆🏅, review👀 your Tasks in CalCentral 💻🖨🖱to make sure your financial aid💸 file🗄🗂 is complete👍 and that you have satisfied 😩💦💦all eligibility requirements for disbursement.🎉🎉🎊
If you are receiving📲💌📬 funding from an outside source 😏👴💦🍆(i.e., agency, scholarship, sponsor), work closely 👉👈with them to disburse 🙌your funds 💸💴💳💎promptly.
If you are paying tuition💰 and fees💳💴 from personal funds😭💵❌, don’t wait until the last minute.⏳⌛️
New this year🎆🎉🎊 is the ability to pay for tuition and fees with a 💳credit card 💳if you prefer.
Starting August 17📅📆, you canapply for an emergency loan 🚑🚓👷to assist you with your fee payment🏥🏥
Clear ❌any holds so that you 👦👧are officially registered 🗳🗃and able to access campus services.📓📗🔗📝
Be sure to read 📖👀your email💻🖥 and monitor CalCentral⌨💽 to stay informed ⌚️of your payment💸💴💰 and enrollment status.👀💯👌
It’s‼️ important ‼️that you take care of paying 💵💳💰your tuition and fees💴😒 before the August 19 deadline📆🗓. By doing so, you will be officially✔️👀👌👌💯 registered (assuming no holds🔙✋), allowing you to retain your class 📓📒📕enrollment status🔍📝 and access to campus services👌👏👏. With your financial 💸💵💴responsibilities taken care of🍾🍺🍻💃, you will be able to focus🙇🏻 on your academic activities📝😎🍁😏😤.

What if You Need Help or Have Questions?

Visit registrar.berkeley.edu/cnp 💻🖱🖨for additional information📡, including deadlines📆 and payment 💸💰options. Make early contact withCal Student Central🏛 if you need support or advice😜🤓.

Sincerely,❌⭕️❌⭕️😘

👴Harry LeGrande👴
Vice Chancellor of Student Affairs, UC Berkeley🐻✏️📕📒
